By preſcribed Forms are meant ſuch as are impoſed upon the Adminiſtrator, ſo as thoſe muſt be uſed, and no other, nor otherwiſe, without adding, detracting, or tranſpoſing. The Favourers of ſuch Forms ſuppoſe, they have been the conſtant uſage of the Church, every where, ever ſince extraordinary gifts ceaſed. Their Oppoſites judge this hath been rather taken for granted, then proved; and ſuſpect they are 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 ; and that this opinion had not got entertainment, but upon a preſumption, that things were ſo of old, becauſe they are ſo now;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . Iſid. Pelul. l. 25. ep. 18.
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . Iſid. l. 3. ep. 191. and that the miſtake had not ſo long prevailed, if it had been ſooner examined.

Amongſt other things, wherewith Athanaſius was falſely charged by the Arrian faction, to make way for his condemnation: Macarius (with reflection upon that great Perſon who imployed him) is accuſed, to have leapt upon the Altar, overthrown the Table, broke the Communion Cup, burnt the Bible; 
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  . Socr. Hiſt. l. 1. c. 20. p. 539.

